            <TextBlock Margin="10,0,0,10" TextWrapping="Wrap" FontSize="11">
                Hornet is a file system interrogation utility that lets you preconfigure and run scans to
                find instances of known files (using hashes) within given file systems, including by disassembling
                some file formats (such as ZIP, PDF, DOCX) and looking at their embedded files, as well as finding patterns of
                text within common file formats (using regular expressions).  It is designed to be run across
                enterprise scale file shares or local disks, and is able to output a PDF report of everything
                it finds.  Hornet is designed to be highly configurable in terms of what to look for and resource
                management, therefore is best suited for relatively technical users.
            </TextBlock>
